==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nugatory
<hw>Nu"ga*to*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>nugatorius</ets>, fr. <ets>nugari</ets> to trifle, <ets>nugae</ets>
jests, trifles.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Trifling; vain; futile;
insignificant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Of no force; inoperative; ineffectual.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If all are pardoned, and pardoned as a mere act of clemency, the
very substance of government is made <qex>nugatory</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>I. Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nugget</ent>⟦br⟧
